    "chemicalDescription": [
      "s-Frog Oligopeptide-1 Amide is a single chain peptide synthetically produced based on a 14 amino acid sequence from Temporin-1DRb which is found in the California red-legged frog, Rana draytonii. Temporin-1DRb has a maximum of 63 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation, and consists of the proper sequence of the 20 amino acids."
